You can find out more in the dashboard here and try with $DPI too! 
https://t.co/uhg3OjeG31

Trading volume looks bimodal - one peak around end of Oct to early Nov, coincided with the timing when Facebook renamed itself Meta; the other peak was towards end of Nov, riding the momentum with other gaming/metaverse tokens.
Currently, almost all trades happen on SushiSwap https://t.co/qSE8vuEZla

65% of the addresses are wallets, which also hold an equivalent share (67%) of MVI unit supply. The rest is held in contracts, in which SushiSwap LP has a balance of 1621, 20% of the unit supply on Polygon.
This is in contrast to DPI, where >70% of the unit supply is in contracts https://t.co/by0Xexb7VV

in case you are not familiar, MVI is a basket of tokens, designed by @indexcoop to capture the trend of the buzzword of 2021 - Metaverse. 
The team has been actively working to offer the index products on Polygon, which provides significant gas savings https://t.co/OzRwMRjnok

had a look into $MVI on @0xPolygon this week and here are some stats:
- 28% of active addresses are now on Polygon
- the unit supply on Polygon represents 4% of the total supply https://t.co/E0fsT5A5Xy
